libusage is a small library that helps you build your usage display quickly and dynamically,
so you don't get bogged down with a bunch of #define . 
Just have a look at the example directory to see how it can be used.

Maybe it'll suit your needs 

* This  programme is not part of GNU C Library *

Build  lib : 
---
$  cmake -S . -B build

Build playground examples 
---
$ cd playground 
$ cmake -S . -B build -DBUILD_EXPLENO=1 #for example_1.c 
$ cmake -S . -B build -DBUILD_EXPLENO=2 #for example_2.c   

-- Happy Hacking Folks ! 
